            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Construct an open mesh from multiple sequences."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "This function takes N 1-D sequences and returns N outputs with N\ndimensions each, such that the shape is 1 in all but one dimension\nand the dimension with the non-unit shape value cycles through all\nN dimensions."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Using "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/ix_",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "ix_",
                "text": "ix_"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " one can quickly construct index arrays that will index\nthe cross product. "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a[we.ix_([1,3],[2,5])]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " returns the array\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "[[a[1,2] a[1,5]], [a[3,2] a[3,5]]]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Extended Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Each sequence should be of integer or boolean type.\nBoolean sequences will be interpreted as boolean masks for the\ncorresponding dimension (equivalent to passing in\n"
